In a major win for shareholders, a federal judge allowed a class-action lawsuit against Tyco International Ltd. and former executives accused of stealing millions.
The retrial of L. Dennis Kozlowski and Mark Swartz in New York involves charges of grand larceny and securities fraud.
Prosecutors highlight extravagant spending, including a $2 million birthday party and lavish apartments.
The defense argues that the accusations are part of a self-serving strategy by the company's directors.
The trial's focus shifts to illegal bonuses and hidden compensation, with a new approach aimed at discrediting the prosecution's evidence.
